# Review and Output Protocol

This file defines the exact format for every Spring Data MongoDB task response.
Read it fully before writing any output. All six sections are mandatory.

-----

## Output Checklist (verify before finishing)

```
[ ] Section A — Discovery Summary        (what MCP + file reads found)
[ ] Section B — Current Flow             (numbered, problems highlighted)
[ ] Section C — Generated Code           (complete files, all imports, project-synced)
[ ] Section D — Recommended Flow         (numbered, maps each fix to each problem)
[ ] Section E — Test Cases               (repo test + service test, both runnable)
[ ] Section F — Review + Rating          (cross-check table + scored dimensions)
```

