## Section D — Recommended Flow

**Purpose:** Show the user how the code works AFTER the changes, step by step.
Each step maps back to a problem from Section B and shows what changed.

```markdown
## D. Recommended Flow (After Changes)

Feature: Get order history for a user

1. GET /api/orders?userId=abc&page=0&size=20 arrives at OrderController.getOrders()
2. Controller calls orderService.getOrderHistory("abc", PageRequest.of(0, 20))
3. Service calls orderRepository.findByUserId("abc", pageable)
   → MongoDB runs: db.orders.find({ user_id: "abc" }).skip(0).limit(20)
   ✅ P1 Fixed: @Field("user_id") → correct field targeted → returns real data
   ✅ P2 Fixed: @Indexed on user_id → IXSCAN → 3000ms → 15ms (200x faster)
   ✅ P3 Fixed: Pageable → 20 docs returned, not all 45K
4. Service maps Page<Order> → Page<OrderSummaryDto>
   ✅ P4 Fixed: DTO response → only safe fields exposed to client
5. Controller returns Page<OrderSummaryDto> with pagination metadata

Data Flow:
  Client
    ↓ GET /api/orders?userId=abc&page=0&size=20
  OrderController.getOrders(userId, page, size)
    ↓ orderService.getOrderHistory(userId, PageRequest.of(0, 20))
  OrderService.getOrderHistory()
    ↓ orderRepository.findByUserId(userId, pageable) — 2 queries: data + count
  MongoDB  →  IXSCAN on user_id_1  →  20 matching docs
    ↓
  OrderService  →  .map(OrderSummaryDto::from)
    ↓
  Client  ←  Page<OrderSummaryDto> { content, totalElements, totalPages, ... }

Performance improvement:
  Before: COLLSCAN, 45,231 docs scanned, ~3000ms, returns all orders in memory
  After:  IXSCAN, ~20 docs scanned, ~15ms, 20 docs paginated
```

