### F.2 Code Quality Review

Strengths:
+ @Field annotations match live MongoDB field names (verified via MCP find)
+ @Indexed and @CompoundIndex match live DB indexes (verified via MCP list_indexes)
+ Pageable on all repo methods (count is 45K — mandatory)
+ Batch loading in service (findAllById + Map) — no N+1
+ DTO response — client sees only what it needs
+ @EnableMongoAuditing + @CreatedDate — consistent with project's existing entities

Limitations:
! Two-query approach (findByUserId + count for Page) — acceptable for this load,
  but consider $facet aggregation if both count and data are needed frequently

Risks:
~ auto-index-creation=true found in application.yml
  Spring will attempt to create indexes on every startup
  Set to false before ANY production or staging deployment
